Three people were left injured on Sunday evening when a train collided with their vehicle at the Ferreira Crossing in Bloemfontein, Free State, according to ER24. ER24 paramedics, along with Life Healthcare and provincial services, arrived on the scene at 18:00 and found the light motor vehicle crushed against the front of the train. The three men in the vehicle already got out and were walking around at the scene. Paramedics assessed the driver and two passengers who had sustained minor to moderate injuries. Fortunately, there were no fatalities. They were treated for their injuries and subsequently transported to nearby provincial hospitals. None of the train passengers sustained any injuries. It is unclear how the vehicle got in the way of the train. Local authorities were on the scene for further investigations.  KEEP UPDATED on the latest news by subscribing to our FREE newsletter. - FOLLOW News24 on Twitter